OL,3,CCompany fined #1.6m after 24-year-old
OL,4,Cman crushed to death
OL,6,FThe company was fined #1,600,000 and
OL,7,Fordered to pay #23,193.60 in costs at
OL,8,FBrighton Magistrates' Court on 27
OL,9,FNovember 2024.
OL,11,FHSE principal inspector Ross Carter
OL,12,Fsaid: "This tragic incident led to the
OL,13,Fwholly avoidable death of a young man.
OL,14,FThis death could so easily have been
OL,15,Fprevented if Jack's employer had
OL,16,Ffulfilled its statutory duty to plan
OL,17,Fand manage the risks associated with
OL,18,Flifting equipment and lifting
OL,19,Foperations.
